==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cowherb
<hw>cowherb</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a European annual with pale
rose-colored flowers; cultivated flower or self-sown grainfield weed;
introduced in North America; sometimes classified as a soapwort; -- also
called the <altname>cow-cockle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cow cockle, cow-cockle, Vaccaria hispanica, Vaccaria
pyramidata, Saponaria vaccaria.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cowherd</ent>⟦br⟧
